I'll start by reading the orchestration contract, then run live web research on Iridium STL, terrestrial SoOP around Danish waters, Danish maritime regs, and CelesTrak SupGP.===R2-DOC===
# U-R2 Research: PNT services, terrestrial SoOP, regulations (live web)

**Access date for all sources:** 2026-07-22  
**Operating-area assumption (flagged):** Danish waters / Danish straits (Øresund, Great Belt, Little Belt, Kattegat approaches). All area-specific inferences below use this assumption unless a source names another basin.  
**Disclaimer (regulatory):** Findings in §3 are **not legal advice**. For binding answers, contact the Danish Maritime Authority (DMA) and, where applicable, the Danish Emergency Management Agency (DEMA). Equivalent EU-level material is descriptive only; flag-state and coastal-state rules control.

**Legend:** **[VERIFIED]** = read on a primary/secondary page this session. **[ASSUMED]** = inference from partial evidence; labelled as such.

---

## 1. Iridium STL (Satelles / Xona — ownership & branding 2026)

### 1.1 Owner / branding — not Xona

**[VERIFIED]** In April 2024 Iridium Communications completed acquisition of Satelles, Inc. (~US$115M for the remaining ~80%; Iridium already held ~20%). The service was rebranded **Iridium Satellite Time and Location (STL)** and is also referred to as **Iridium PNT**.  
Sources:  
- https://investor.iridium.com/2024-04-02-Iridium-Completes-Satelles-Acquisition-Introduces-Iridium-Satellite-Time-and-Location-STL (access 2026-07-22)  
- https://www.gpsworld.com/iridium-acquires-satelles-to-boost-pnt-capabilities/ (access 2026-07-22)  
- https://www.iridium.com/iridium-pnt/solutions/timing/nist (access 2026-07-22) — states Satelles is “formerly known as” / STL “now referred to broadly as Iridium PNT”

**[VERIFIED]** **Xona Space Systems** is a **separate** company offering a dedicated LEO PNT constellation brand **Pulsar** (demo Pulsar-0; production launches targeted late 2026 / early service ~2027). It is **not** the owner of Iridium STL.  
Sources:  
- https://www.xonaspace.com/ (access 2026-07-22)  
- https://arstechnica.com/space/2026/07/move-over-gps-navigation-satellites-in-low-earth-orbit-are-making-a-comeback/ (access 2026-07-22)  
- FrontierSI LEO PNT market report (2025 edition, published 2026): Iridium PNT described as the only fully operational commercial LEO PNT service at end-2025 — https://frontiersi.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/FrontierSI-State-of-Market-Report-LEO-PNT-2025-Edition-v1.0-3.pdf (access 2026-07-22)

### 1.2 Product status (2026)

**[VERIFIED]** Operational commercial service on the existing Iridium LEO constellation (encrypted alternate PNT; receive-only from user perspective in standard descriptions). Expanded commercial partner sales authorization for **parts of Europe and Asia-Pacific** announced June 2024 (signal is globally available; sales geography is licensed through partners).  
Sources:  
- https://investor.iridium.com/2024-06-20-Iridium-Satellite-Time-and-Location-Service-Activated-for-Europe-and-Asia-Pacific-Regions (access 2026-07-22)  
- Iridium NIST collaboration page updated through Jan 2026 papers (access 2026-07-22)

**[ASSUMED]** For a Danish-waters project, Europe partner sales channel is the intended commercial path; confirm current partner list with Iridium (geographic authorization language is “parts of Europe”).

### 1.3 Receiver hardware options

**[VERIFIED]** Commercial modules / integrated products exist; examples:

| Product / line | Vendor | Notes | Source (access 2026-07-22) |
|---|---|---|---|
| STL-2600 LEO receiver module | VIAVI (heritage Jackson Labs) | GNSS-independent timing + meters-class stationary positioning; designed for SecureTime LEO / Iridium STL | https://www.viavisolutions.com/en-us/products/stl-2600-low-earth-orbit-receiver-module |
| Secure microPNT STL-1000 | VIAVI | Compact SDR module; datasheet states lock requires **active subscription** to Iridium-based SecureTime LEO | https://www.viavisolutions.com/en-us/literature/secure-micropnt-stl-1000-leo-receiver-module-data-sheets-en.pdf |
| Partner GNSS+STL boxes | VIAVI, Adtran, Safran (named) | “STL upgrade” / GNSS+STL drop-in products | https://insidegnss.com/iridium-stl-protecting-pnt-as-part-of-a-layered-approach/ (2025) |

**[VERIFIED]** Auburn University thesis used commercial Jackson Labs **STL-2600** receivers for timing evaluation.  
Source: https://etd.auburn.edu/handle/10415/9082 (access 2026-07-22)

### 1.4 How purchased; public pricing; path to quote

**[VERIFIED]** Model is **commercial service + partner hardware**, not free like GNSS:

- Iridium sells through partner ecosystem (~500 partners broadly; PNT-specific partners include VIAVI, Adtran, Safran).  
- VIAVI **SecureTime LEO** product pages state “Request a Quote”; STL lock on modules “requires active subscription to Iridium based SecureTime LEO services.”  
- Iridium public contact for STL: **pnt@iridium.com**; product page path historically https://www.iridium.com/satellite-time-location (redirect/branding may now sit under /iridium-pnt).  
- Reseller example (GIT Satellite) lists “Call for price.”

Sources:  
- https://investor.iridium.com/2024-06-20-Iridium-Satellite-Time-and-Location-Service-Activated-for-Europe-and-Asia-Pacific-Regions (access 2026-07-22)  
- https://www.viavisolutions.com/en-us/products/securetime-leo-services (access 2026-07-22)  
- https://www.viavisolutions.com/en-us/literature/secure-micropnt-stl-1000-leo-receiver-module-data-sheets-en.pdf (access 2026-07-22)  
- https://insidegnss.com/iridium-stl-protecting-pnt-as-part-of-a-layered-approach/ (access 2026-07-22)

**[VERIFIED]** **No public list prices** found for service subscription or OEM silicon/module volume pricing on vendor pages this session.

**Concrete quote path (actionable):**  
1. Email **pnt@iridium.com** stating use case (marine experimental PNT, Denmark/EU), volume, timing vs position needs.  
2. In parallel, VIAVI sales quote for SecureTime LEO + STL-2600 / STL-1000 (https://www.viavisolutions.com/en-us/contact-sales or product “Request a Quote”).  
3. Optionally contact Adtran / Safran for GNSS+STL appliance paths.

### 1.5 Claimed performance (~20 m, sub-100 ns) — vendor vs independent

| Claim | Status | Evidence |
|---|---|---|
| **Position ~20 m** (standalone, after convergence) | **[VERIFIED]** as long-standing vendor/historical claim | Inside GNSS (2016, Satelles/Iridium): ~50 m in ~2 min, **20 m or better after ~10 min**; with aiding “as good as 5 m, 1σ”. GPS World innovation article: “positioning accuracy of 20 meters”. UNOOSA LEO-PNT workshop slide pack (Satelles): “Positioning accuracies of ~10 meters”. Sources: https://insidegnss.com/iridium-based-system-proposed-gps-backup-incorporates-crypto-protections/ ; https://www.gpsworld.com/innovation-navigation-from-leo/ ; https://www.unoosa.org/documents/pdf/icg/2023/ICG_WG-S_LEO-PNT_Workshop_June_2023/ICG_LEO-PNT_Workshop_2023_05.pdf (all access 2026-07-22) |
| **Timing sub-100 ns** | **[VERIFIED]** for calibrated receivers with good oscillators under lab conditions | NIST/Satelles joint work: average offsets near 10 ns (OCXO), max &lt;200 ns; Rb max &lt;75 ns; long-term average offset &lt;1 ns after calibration; MTIE &lt;100 ns (PRTC-A class) with quality oscillators. Jan 2026 NIST paper: MAC oscillator, max offset &lt;40 ns, MTIE &lt;80 ns over 40 days (improved with ionospheric corrections). Iridium page summarizes these. Sources: https://www.iridium.com/iridium-pnt/solutions/timing/nist ; https://www.nist.gov/publications/validating-timing-performance-improvement-ionospheric-corrections-iridium-pnt-receivers ; https://www.nist.gov/publications/measuring-timing-accuracy-satellite-time-and-location-stl-receivers (access 2026-07-22) |
| **Timing sub-μs indoors / attenuated** | **[VERIFIED]** | GPS World: “timekeeping to within 1 microsecond… deep attenuation”; sub-100 ns with Rb at unknown static indoor location in further demos. Source: https://www.gpsworld.com/innovation-navigation-from-leo/ (access 2026-07-22) |
| **Maritime dynamic position accuracy at Danish latitudes** | **[ASSUMED] / not verified this session** | Public literature emphasizes timing and static/critical-infrastructure use; dynamic marine accuracy under multipath/sea motion not independently confirmed here. |

**Bottom line on the brief’s “~20 m, sub-100 ns”:**  
- **~20 m position:** supported by vendor historical claims and field-test write-ups; treat as **order-of-magnitude** for unaided positioning after minutes of convergence, not a certified maritime accuracy standard.  
- **Sub-100 ns timing:** **well supported** by NIST joint evaluations for appropriate oscillator class and calibration — stronger claim than position for scientific evidence quality.

