## Cross-cutting notes for Danish waters (assumption)

| Source | Relevance to Danish waters / straits (assumption) | Confidence |
|---|---|---|
| Iridium STL | Global LEO; commercially sellable in parts of Europe via partners | High (service); medium (partner SKU availability) |
| DVB-T2 SoOP | Strong candidate nearshore/straits | Medium (sync architecture unconfirmed) |
| R-Mode | SW Baltic testbed may illuminate southern approaches; not DK-native network | Medium |
| Public cellular | Good in straits; offshore patchy | Medium-high |
| Tampnet LTE | Relevant if ops extend to Danish North Sea shelf | High for North Sea industrial zones |
| eLoran | Not operational PNT layer for DK in 2026 | High |
| CelesTrak SupGP | Independent of geography; Starlink/OneWeb dense at DK latitudes | High |

